# Core Conventions
- TypeScript strict mode — never use `any`, use `unknown` or define a type
- Named exports only — never default exports
- All async functions must use try/catch with proper error handling
- Use `bun` as the package manager
- Keep files under 200 lines; split when they grow larger
- Write self-documenting code; add comments only for "why", not "what"